TITLE: 3 trends are dividing restaurant companies into winners and losers
SUMMARY: While most restaurant companies crushed earnings expectations, a number of them fell short of Wall Street's estimates for their quarterly revenue.

TITLE: What Wall Street needs to know about UAW talks, a potential strike and what it could all cost
SUMMARY: Contracts between the Detroit automakers and United Auto Workers union expire at 11:59 p.m. ET on Sept. 14.

TITLE: Automakers are finally embracing lidar sensors. A few startups look like market-share winners
SUMMARY: After years of talk — and a SPAC boom in the sensor sector — automakers have finally started incorporating lidar units into their vehicles.

TITLE: New Covid vaccines from Pfizer, Moderna and Novavax will likely protect against Eris variant
SUMMARY: The drugmakers designed their updated coronavirus shots to target the omicron subvariant XBB.1.5, which is slowly declining nationwide.

TITLE: 'Barbie' faces DC's 'Blue Beetle' in a late summer box office showdown
SUMMARY: Warner Bros. Discovery's "Blue Beetle" arrives in cinemas this weekend and is expected to tally between $22 million and $32 million domestically.

TITLE: Outback Steakhouse owner's stock rises after activist Starboard Value buys stake
SUMMARY: Starboard Value now owns 9.9% of Bloomin' Brands' shares, according to a regulatory filing.

TITLE: Moderna says new Covid vaccine was effective against Eris variant in early trial
SUMMARY: Moderna's vaccine and new shots from Pfizer and Novavax are slated to roll out within weeks, pending potential approvals from the Food and Drug Administration.

TITLE: Walmart and Target face similar problems — but only one is thriving
SUMMARY: The two big-box retailers' fiscal second-quarter results had sharp differences, even as economic factors shape consumer spending.

TITLE: 'Dune: Part Two' is supposed to come out this year. The strikes could change that
SUMMARY: Due to dual Hollywood labor strikes, studios are being forced to decide between releasing films without actor promotions or push openings to next year.

TITLE: Looming auto workers strike could cost $5 billion in just 10 days, new analysis says
SUMMARY: A work stoppage by nearly 150,000 UAW workers would result in an economic loss of more than $5 billion after 10 days, according to Anderson Economic Group.

TITLE: Weight-loss drugs are priced substantially higher in the U.S. than in other countries, analysis says
SUMMARY: The KFF analysis comes as many U.S. health insurers balk at the extreme cost of weight-loss drugs and drop the medications from their plans.

TITLE: Walmart raises full-year earnings forecast as grocery, online growth fuel higher sales
SUMMARY: Walmart beat earnings and revenue expectations as it capitalizes on its low-priced reputation with consumers looking for value.

TITLE: CVS stock plunges after Blue Shield of California drops retailer's pharmacy services to save on drug costs
SUMMARY: Blue Shield's announcement hints at the potential for health insurers to abandon the traditional pharmacy benefit management system.

TITLE: SpaceX reportedly turned a profit in the first quarter
SUMMARY: The rare look at SpaceX's financials offers a clue into how the company is faring while it ramps up Starlink and races to get the Starship rocket flying.

TITLE: Diamond Sports calls in mediators as it pushes toward a reorganization plan
SUMMARY: Diamond Sports called on mediators step into its conversations with creditors as it tries to solidify a reorganization plan ahead of the NBA and NHL seasons.

TITLE: Several Buy Buy Baby, Harmon stores to reopen after buyers scored deals on the bankrupt brands
SUMMARY: The new owners of Buy Buy Baby plan to reopen 11 stores as soon as this fall while Harmon is coming back, too, after Bed Bath & Beyond's bankruptcy.

TITLE: UK defense contractor BAE buying Ball's aerospace division for $5.6 billion
SUMMARY: Ball began shopping around its aerospace division earlier this year, looking for a deal that would help trim its nearly $10 billion in debt.

TITLE: Blue Shield of California taps Amazon, Mark Cuban's Cost Plus Drugs for its pharmacy network
SUMMARY: The nonprofit health insurer, with 4.8 million members, expects the move to the low-cost pharmacies will provide $500 million in annual savings on drug costs.

TITLE: Wegovy could prevent up to 1.5 million heart attacks, strokes over 10 years, study says
SUMMARY: The results complement the data Novo Nordisk released last week, which found Wegovy slashed the risk of serious heart problems and heart-related death by 20%.

TITLE: Target Pride backlash adds to sales woes as culture wars rage in corporate America
SUMMARY: As Target reported earnings, CEO Brian Cornell defended the company's decision to pull some merchandise, but said it will continue to celebrate Pride month.

TITLE: 'Barbie' beats Batman, becomes Warner Bros.' highest-grossing domestic release
SUMMARY: "Barbie" has topped $537 million, making it the highest-grossing domestic movie in Warner Bros. Discovery's 100-year history.

TITLE: Shoppers are spending big at T.J. Maxx, HomeGoods as Target sales slide
SUMMARY: TJX Cos., which runs T.J. Maxx and Marshalls, is seeing big gains in discretionary purchases as cash-strapped consumers look for a deal amid high inflation.

TITLE: Cava and Sweetgreen see delivery orders fall as customers pick up their own food
SUMMARY: Delivery orders are usually more expensive due to added fees and even higher menu prices.

TITLE: Aldi to acquire Winn-Dixie and Harveys Supermarket stores in Southern expansion
SUMMARY: The German grocer has entered into an agreement to buy about 400 store locations from Winn-Dixie and Harveys Supermarket.

TITLE: General Motors is investing in a startup working on better and cheaper EV batteries
SUMMARY: GM is leading a $60 million funding round in Mitra Chem, a battery startup founded by Tesla and Toyota veterans that aims to make cheaper EV batteries.

TITLE: Target slashes full-year earnings forecast as retailer struggles to win over thrifty shoppers
SUMMARY: Target cut its full-year forecast even as recession fears fade, as the retailer cited factors like still high prices and the restart of student loan payments.

TITLE: Look inside the $44.5 million Tuscan-style mega villa perched 2,000 feet above Malibu
SUMMARY: "If you have a God complex, this is the house for you," says the listing agent for the estate.

TITLE: Weekly mortgage demand drops again, as interest rates match a 22-year high
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates rose for the third straight week last week, matching a 22-year high. As a result, mortgage demand dropped as well.

TITLE: Young people are at risk of harsh respiratory problems after 30 days of e-cigarette use, study says
SUMMARY: Researchers urged drug regulators to consider the study findings and work to minimize the negative impact of electronic cigarette use on young people.

TITLE: Disney accused of withholding hundreds of millions of dollars from 'Avatar' sequel financier
SUMMARY: Disney has been accused of withholding profits from TSG Entertainment, a long-time financing partner of its 20th Century Fox studio.
